      "text": "A 71-year-old woman with a history of COPD, diastolic heart failure, and chronic kidney disease presents to the ED with 3 days of cough, fatigue, and increasing shortness of breath. She denies chest pain or sputum production. Vital signs are BP, 110/66 mm Hg; P, 104; R, 24; T, 37.9°C (100.2°F); SpO₂, 91% on room air. Her baseline SpO₂ is 90–92%. On examination, she has mild accessory muscle use and scattered wheezes bilaterally. Chest radiograph shows peribronchial cuffing and mild interstitial markings without consolidation. Respiratory syncytial virus antigen test is positive; influenza and SARS-CoV-2 are negative. Laboratory studies show BUN 28 mg/dL, creatinine 1.6 mg/dL, BNP 310 pg/mL, and WBC 8.2 ×10³/mm³. Which is the most appropriate management for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Discharge with empiric broad-spectrum antibiotics for pneumonia and close outpatient follow-up"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Discharge with oral bronchodilators and close outpatient follow-up"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Admit for supportive care and monitoring"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Admit for nebulized ribavirin and supportive care"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Admit for nirsevimab and supportive care"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>The absence of consolidation, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wF0h43&anker=Zb1919b7d94d10a63debcb709eaa693f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"wF0h43\" data-anker=\"Zb1919b7d94d10a63debcb709eaa693f3\" data-sememe-id=\"ylYdz6\">leukocytosis</a>, or high <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> makes bacterial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a> unlikely. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-section-id=\"2acTPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"qkYCK6\">RSV</a> is a viral <span data-sememe-id=\"XgW9Fk0\">pathogen</span>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotic therapy</a> would not improve her outcome.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>While her <span data-sememe-id=\"GPWBTl0\">SpO₂</span> is at baseline, her multiple comorbidities put her at risk of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=m80VM3&anker=Z7dbad05f9d85b11c4ef01824174babcc\" data-learningcard-id=\"m80VM3\" data-anker=\"Z7dbad05f9d85b11c4ef01824174babcc\" data-section-id=\"TzW6HL0\">severe RSV infection</a>, and her early <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tH0XHh&anker=Z5ccba71c35a8e64793ca0ac9cd9c690f\" data-learningcard-id=\"tH0XHh\" data-anker=\"Z5ccba71c35a8e64793ca0ac9cd9c690f\" data-section-id=\"i-1JCj0\" data-sememe-id=\"DH11sR0\">signs of respiratory distress</a> make discharge unsafe. She requires observation for potential decompensation.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>Correct – This patient’s positive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-section-id=\"2acTPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"qkYCK6\">RSV</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"CN1qWh0\">antigen</span> test confirms a viral <span data-sememe-id=\"5qci_W0\">lower respiratory tract infection</span>. Although her <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=EJ08DS&anker=Zcdfc30b72bdf1b54bf2c4a1b18b109c4\" data-learningcard-id=\"EJ08DS\" data-anker=\"Zcdfc30b72bdf1b54bf2c4a1b18b109c4\" data-section-id=\"2X1Tx20\" data-sememe-id=\"UlXbwy\">oxygen saturation</a> is at baseline, her <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tl0XAT&anker=Z9f745914c0340ad3beed72e989c555ff\" data-learningcard-id=\"tl0XAT\" data-anker=\"Z9f745914c0340ad3beed72e989c555ff\" data-section-id=\"sCXttZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"Jj0sYT\">tachypnea</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tH0XHh&anker=Z4a04ad8809a397c6381eff4aff865aae\" data-learningcard-id=\"tH0XHh\" data-anker=\"Z4a04ad8809a397c6381eff4aff865aae\" data-section-id=\"i-1JCj0\" data-sememe-id=\"x8cEKV0\">increased work of breathing</a> indicate early respiratory compromise. Advanced age and comorbid conditions (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3h0Sdf&anker=Ze02d225158d496610d00b7f2469fca56\" data-learningcard-id=\"3h0Sdf\" data-anker=\"Ze02d225158d496610d00b7f2469fca56\" data-sememe-id=\"Lk0woT\">COPD</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rS0faf&anker=Z07d22fa4c3f9da63ddf39683e4eaa845\" data-learningcard-id=\"rS0faf\" data-anker=\"Z07d22fa4c3f9da63ddf39683e4eaa845\" data-sememe-id=\"ak0QmT\">heart failure</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lg0vv2&anker=Zeb975888cde4515672ab89a7a3068ab2\" data-learningcard-id=\"lg0vv2\" data-anker=\"Zeb975888cde4515672ab89a7a3068ab2\" data-sememe-id=\"W40PRT\">CKD</a>) increase her risk for rapid deterioration. Admission for observation and supportive care is the safest management approach.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Inhaled <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pm0Lgg&anker=Z18a8b3fbdf430fc0b02a7a0b68ddcfd3\" data-learningcard-id=\"pm0Lgg\" data-anker=\"Z18a8b3fbdf430fc0b02a7a0b68ddcfd3\" data-section-id=\"wBXh100\" data-sememe-id=\"FWYgML\">ribavirin</a> is only licensed for use in children with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=m80VM3&anker=Z7dbad05f9d85b11c4ef01824174babcc\" data-learningcard-id=\"m80VM3\" data-anker=\"Z7dbad05f9d85b11c4ef01824174babcc\" data-section-id=\"TzW6HL0\">severe RSV infection</a> and is not routinely indicated for managing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=m80VM3&anker=Zb6666d414f20f97f6dc15976839b37a8\" data-learningcard-id=\"m80VM3\" data-anker=\"Zb6666d414f20f97f6dc15976839b37a8\">RSV infection</a>. Its use in adults is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7N04cg&anker=Zb37ab5e3f79a4ddd6b356eb84fa0067a\" data-learningcard-id=\"7N04cg\" data-anker=\"Zb37ab5e3f79a4ddd6b356eb84fa0067a\" data-section-id=\"3BXS000\" data-sememe-id=\"Jh0sUf\">off-label</a> and generally limited to severely <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-section-id=\"h_XcL00\" data-sememe-id=\"P2YW3o\">immunocompromised</a> patients with life-threatening disease.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=m80VM3&anker=Zf70f775456dbab554e5d7a3cb7965c7c\" data-learningcard-id=\"m80VM3\" data-anker=\"Zf70f775456dbab554e5d7a3cb7965c7c\" data-section-id=\"3zWSsL0\" data-sememe-id=\"qsdCDr0\">Nirsevimab</a> is a long-acting <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=gp0FKS&anker=Z86a7bedbcdf934db12cabdde22b280f6\" data-learningcard-id=\"gp0FKS\" data-anker=\"Z86a7bedbcdf934db12cabdde22b280f6\" data-section-id=\"u9cp6e0\" data-sememe-id=\"lBXva00\">monoclonal antibody</a> licensed for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oL00Ag&anker=Z213837a578831ac540dbc405f1dcc2dc\" data-learningcard-id=\"oL00Ag\" data-anker=\"Z213837a578831ac540dbc405f1dcc2dc\" data-section-id=\"Ufcblb0\">prevention of RSV</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pu0Wr3&anker=Z864bb7e50db75e39e6bfd3ac64ebb34a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pu0Wr3\" data-anker=\"Z864bb7e50db75e39e6bfd3ac64ebb34a\" data-section-id=\"7dd4rK0\" data-sememe-id=\"1gW28k0\">lower respiratory tract</a> disease in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z6f0fa51eb81a7d03aa179eab82aacab8\" data-sememe-id=\"-m0DRg\">neonates</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=a40Q3T&anker=Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-learningcard-id=\"a40Q3T\" data-anker=\"Z0fc257b9a869b8bf01b45c4fb73dbdc1\" data-section-id=\"_8X56-\" data-sememe-id=\"4Qb3wt\">infants</a> (and selected children up to 24 months), not for treatment of active <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=m80VM3&anker=Zb6666d414f20f97f6dc15976839b37a8\" data-learningcard-id=\"m80VM3\" data-anker=\"Zb6666d414f20f97f6dc15976839b37a8\">RSV infection</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=m80VM3&anker=Zf70f775456dbab554e5d7a3cb7965c7c\" data-learningcard-id=\"m80VM3\" data-anker=\"Zf70f775456dbab554e5d7a3cb7965c7c\" data-section-id=\"3zWSsL0\" data-sememe-id=\"qsdCDr0\">Nirsevimab</a> has not been approved or established as therapy for adults.</div>",
